This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with modeling rigid body motion from raw point cloud data. It is also likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it involves predicting the motion of objects resulting from an applied force, which is relevant to robotics. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on predicting object motion in a scene suggests that it could also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
